header.gameNote: LOU HENSON CLASSIC AT LAS CRUCES NM

article.headline: North Texas 75, New Mexico St. 72
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. (AP) -- Collin Dennis scored 21 points as North Texas erased a 21-point deficit to beat New Mexico State 75-72 Saturday night in a second round game of the Lou Henson Classic. Dennis scored all his points in the second half for the Mean Green (5-1), which also got 15 points from freshman Josh White. Justin Hawkins had 28 points and Fred Peete 24 for New Mexico State (3-6), which led by 21 with 14:20 remaining in the game. North Texas pulled to within 54-45 with 11:40 left on a 13-2 run and then closed to 60-55 on Tristan Thompson's 3-pointer. New Mexico State coach Marvin Menzies drew a technical foul while disputing a call and Thompson made the resulting free throw. Dennis' jumper made it 60-58 and Thompson drove to the basket to tie the score at 62 with 6:11 left. The lead see-sawed until White hit a 3-pointer and then made two free throws with 1:21 to play to put the Mean Green ahead 73-70. He added two more foul shots with 11.4 seconds left to seal the victory.
